1️⃣ Do You Need to Write Routes in web.php?

❌ No, you don’t need to write routes manually.

When you installed Filament, it automatically creates the admin panel routes for you.

So you do NOT need to add anything in routes/web.php for:

Users

Roles

Sellers

Buyers

Items

Sales

Filament automatically registers routes like:

/admin/users
/admin/roles
/admin/sellers
/admin/buyers
/admin/items
/admin/sales

You just open:

http://localhost:8000/admin

and the admin panel appears.

2️⃣ When Tables Are Created They Will Be Empty — Is That Normal?

✅ Yes, that is completely normal.

When you run:

php artisan migrate

Laravel only creates table structure, not the data.

Example:

roles table (after migration)
id	name
(empty)	
3️⃣ How Will You Insert Data Into Tables?

There are 3 ways.

Method 1️⃣ Using Filament Admin Panel (Easiest)

After creating Filament resources and running the server:

php artisan serve

Open:

http://localhost:8000/admin

Now you will see menu items like:

Roles
Users
Sellers
Buyers
Items
Sales

Example:

Click Roles → Create Role

Add:

Admin
Seller
Buyer
Staff

Save.

Now roles table will look like:

id	name
1	Admin
2	Seller
3	Buyer
4	Staff
Method 2️⃣ Using Database Seeder (Professional Way)

Create seeder:

php artisan make:seeder RoleSeeder

Then in:

database/seeders/RoleSeeder.php

Add:

use App\Models\Role;

public function run()
{
    Role::create(['name' => 'Admin']);
    Role::create(['name' => 'Seller']);
    Role::create(['name' => 'Buyer']);
    Role::create(['name' => 'Staff']);
}

Run:

php artisan db:seed --class=RoleSeeder

This will insert the roles automatically.

Method 3️⃣ Manually from Database

You can open phpMyAdmin and insert rows manually.

But this is not recommended in professional projects.

